gory:National sports teams of Venezuela|Fed Cup]]\n\n\n{{FedCup-stub}}\n{{Venezuela-sport-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox tennis cup team\n| Name               = Venezuela\n| Type               = Fed\n| Image              = Flag of Venezuela.svg\n| Nickname           = \n| Captain            = [[Yohny Romero]]\n| Coach              = \n| ITF Rank = 45 {{decrease}} 2 (16 November 2015)\n| ITF max = \n| ITF max date = \n| ITF min = \n| ITF min date = \n| Colors             = \n| First year         = [[1984 Federation Cup (tennis)|1984]]\n| Years played       = 24\n| Ties played        = 96 (54\u201342)\n| WG played          = 1 (0\u20131)\n| Titles             =  <!-- leave blank if no titles -->\n| Runners-up         =  <!-- leave blank if no runners-up -->\n| Best               = World Group Play-offs ([[1998 Fed Cup|1998]], [[2001 Fed Cup|2001]])\n| Player wins        = [[Milagros Sequera]] (36\u201311)\n| Singles wins       = Milagros Sequera (23\u20135)\n| Doubles wins       = [[Mar\u00eda Vento-Kabchi]] (14\u20139)\n| Best doubles       = Milagros Sequera /<br/>Mar\u00eda Vento-Kabchi (11\u20135)\n| Most ties          = Mar\u00eda Vento-Kabchi (33)\n| Most years         = Mar\u00eda Vento-Kabchi (8)\n}}\n\nThe '''Venezuela Fed Cup team''' represents [[Venezuela]] in [[Fed Cup]] [[tennis]] competition and are governed by the [[Federaci\u00f3n Venezolana de Tenis]]. Venezuela will compete in Americas Zone Group I in 2012. \n\n==History==\nVenezuela competed in its first Fed Cup in [[1984 Federation Cup (tennis)|1984]].  Their best result was reaching the World Group Play-offs in [[1998 Fed Cup|1998]] and [[2001 Fed Cup|2001]].\n\n==Current team (2017)==\n* [[Andrea G\u00e1miz]]\n* [[Aymet Uzc\u00e1tegui]]\n* [[Adriana P\u00e9rez]]\n* [[Maria Gabriela Linares de Far\u00eda]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[Fed Cup]]\n*[[Venezuela Davis Cup team]]\n\n==External links==\n*{{FedCupteamlink|code=VEN}}\n\n{{National sports teams of Venezuela}}\n{{Fed Cup}}\n\n[[Category:Fed Cup t